## C. MMSE Data Estimate

In this section, we aim to calculate the optimum receiver $\mathbf{g}_{1} \in \mathbb{C}^{N_{r} \times 1}$ that estimates the transmitted data symbol of the tagged user which is denoted by $s_{1}(i) \in \mathbb{C}$. We assume that the transmitted data vector of the tagged user has zero mean with variance $P_{\mathrm{d}, 1}$. Specifically, the BS estimates the data transmitted vector of the tagged user at time slot $i$ based on channel estimates provided at $i$. Then, the optimum MMSE receiver combiner is provided via the following proposition whose proof is provided in Appendix E.

Proposition 2. Let $\mathbf{P}_{c}$ of size $N \times N$ be the commutation matrix which transforms the vectorized version of a matrix to the vectorized version of its transpose. Then, the MMSE optimum receiver given the prior information $\widehat{\mathbf{h}}_{1}(i)$ is obtained as follows:

$$
\mathbf{g}_{1}^{\mathrm{T}}(i) \triangleq \arg \min _{\mathbf{g}_{1} \in \mathbb{C}^{N_{r} \times 1}} \mathrm{E}_{\mathrm{s}_{1}\left[\widehat{\mathbf{h}}_{1}(i)\right]}\left[\left\|\mathbf{g}_{1}^{\mathrm{H}} \mathbf{y}-s_{1}\right\|^{2}\right]=\alpha_{1} \sqrt{P_{\mathrm{d}, 1}} \mathbf{F}(i)^{-1} \widehat{\mathbf{H}}_{1}(i) \mathbf{w}_{1}^{\mathrm{T}}
$$

where

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \mathbf{F}(i) \triangleq \sum_{k=1}^{K} \alpha_{k}^{2} A_{k}\left(\mathbf{D}_{k}\right)+\sigma_{2}^{2} \mathbf{I}_{N_{r}}, \mathbf{D}_{k} \triangleq \mathbf{Q}_{k}+\widehat{\mathbf{h}}_{k}(i) \widehat{\mathbf{h}}_{k}(i)^{H} \\
& \mathbf{D}_{k} \triangleq\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
\mathbf{D}_{k}^{(1,1)} & \ldots & \mathbf{D}_{k}^{\left(1, N_{r}\right)} \\
\vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
\mathbf{D}_{k}^{\left(N_{r}, 1\right)} & \ldots & \mathbf{D}_{k}^{\left(N_{r}, N_{r}\right)}
\end{array}\right], \widehat{\mathbf{H}}_{k} \triangleq \operatorname{vec}^{-1}\left(\widehat{\mathbf{h}}_{k}\right), \mathbf{Q}_{k} \triangleq \mathbf{C}_{\mathbf{h}_{k}(i)}-\mathbf{C}_{\widehat{\mathbf{h}}_{k}(i)} \\
& \mathcal{A}_{k}\left(\mathbf{D}_{k}\right) \triangleq\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
\left\langle\mathbf{D}_{k}^{(1,1)}, \mathbf{C}_{\mathbf{x}_{\mathrm{e}}}\right\rangle & \ldots & \left\langle\mathbf{D}_{k}^{\left(1, N_{r}\right)}, \mathbf{C}_{\mathbf{x}_{\mathrm{e}}}\right\rangle \\
\vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
\left\langle\mathbf{D}_{k}^{\left(N_{r}, 1\right)}, \mathbf{C}_{\mathbf{x}_{\mathrm{e}}}\right\rangle & \ldots & \left\langle\mathbf{D}_{k}^{\left(N_{r}, N_{r}\right)}, \mathbf{C}_{\mathbf{x}_{\mathrm{e}}}\right\rangle
\end{array}\right], \mathbf{D}^{\prime}{ }_{k} \triangleq \mathbf{P}_{c}^{\mathrm{H}} \mathbf{D}_{k} \mathbf{P}_{c}
\end{aligned}
$$

These results serve as a starting point for deriving the achievable SINR and spectral efficiency in the next subsection.
